<div><div><h2>--</h2></div><div>there is an increase in demand for chief diversity officers in the fmcg and fmcd  retail  life sciences  it and engineering/manufacturing sectors  shows a survey of over 100 organisations carried out by bti executive search. “in the it sector  where most women are hired for software testing than programming  there is a focus on hiring more women for programming. similarly  in the engineering sector  there is a push on hiring as well as giving opportunities to women in leadership roles beyond r&d;  production  project  etc. also  companies are willing to experiment with different backgrounds ” said james agrawal  managing director of bti executive search. et looks at the reasons for the spike in demand and the skillsets companies are looking at.</div></div>